# Figma Workflow

## Design File

https://www.figma.com/design/4LFRzDFgPl60EyEnYsiCSW/My-Personal-Blog-Project?node-id=19-2724

## When Implementing UI

1. Read the target Figma frame via Figma MCP tools first
2. Compare with existing components in `src/components/` and `src/components/ui/`
3. Map colors and spacing to tokens in `src/styles/index.css` or shadcn variables
4. Reuse `@/components/ui/*` primitives before writing custom markup
5. After implementation, verify spacing, typography, and colors against the Figma frame

## MCP Fallback

- Primary: remote Figma MCP (`https://mcp.figma.com/mcp`) via Figma plugin
- Fallback: Figma Desktop Dev Mode MCP at `http://127.0.0.1:3845/mcp` (requires Figma desktop app with file open in Dev Mode)
